<figureCitation box="[944,1028,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–15" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[222,1406,262,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[184,1407,193,1923]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 13–15. Male hypopygium, lateral view. 13. Amblypsilopus marginatus sp. nov.; 14. Amblypsilopus medogensis sp. nov.; 15. Amblypsilopus quinquepetalus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: epn = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus, sur = surstylus, lat = lateral lobe, cer = cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2628508/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
